## Interaction Contract

- Fallback priority is image, default slot, `icon`, initials from `name`, then the default `user` icon.
- Image load errors switch to the same non-image fallback chain.
- Initials use the first character of the first word and, when present, the first character of the last word.
- `size` accepts preset sizes, positive numbers, positive numeric strings, and positive px strings. Invalid custom sizes fall back to preset styling.
- Custom numeric sizes set CSS variables for avatar size, font size, status dot size, and status border width.
- `backgroundColor` also sets `textColor`; when `textColor` is omitted it falls back to white.
- `click` emits only when `clickable=true`.
- `TxAvatarGroup` preserves child props, injects group `size` only into children without their own size, and renders `+N` for hidden children when `max` is lower than the child count.

## API

### Props

#### TxAvatar

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|------|------|---------|-------------|
| `src` | `string` | - | Avatar image URL. |
| `alt` | `string` | - | Image alt text. Provide it when `src` is meaningful content. |
| `name` | `string` | - | Name used to generate initials fallback. |
| `icon` | `string` | - | Icon name passed to `TxIcon`. |
| `size` | `'small' \| 'medium' \| 'large' \| 'xlarge' \| number \| \`${number}\` \| \`${number}px\`` | `'medium'` | Preset or custom avatar size. Positive custom numbers and px strings write runtime size variables. |
| `status` | `'online' \| 'offline' \| 'busy' \| 'away'` | - | Status dot rendered in the avatar corner. |
| `shape` | `'circle' \| 'square' \| 'rounded'` | `'circle'` | Avatar shape class. |
| `clickable` | `boolean` | `false` | Enables clickable styling and allows the `click` event to emit. |
| `backgroundColor` | `string` | - | Custom fallback background color; writes `--tx-avatar-bg`. |
| `textColor` | `string` | `'#ffffff'` when `backgroundColor` is set | Custom fallback text color; writes `--tx-avatar-text` only with `backgroundColor`. |

#### TxAvatarGroup

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|------|------|---------|-------------|
| `max` | `number` | child count | Maximum visible child avatars before rendering the `+N` overflow avatar. Values below zero behave as zero. |
| `size` | `AvatarSize` | - | Size injected into child avatars that do not define their own size. |
| `overlap` | `number \| string` | `8` | Overlap distance. Numbers become px values and are applied as negative margin between avatars. |

### Events

#### TxAvatar

| Event | Payload | Description |
|------|---------|-------------|
| `click` | - | Emitted when the root is clicked and `clickable=true`. |

#### TxAvatarGroup

No public events are emitted.

### Slots

#### TxAvatar

| Slot | Props | Description |
|------|------|-------------|
| `default` | - | Custom fallback content. Takes priority over `icon` and `name`. |

#### TxAvatarGroup

| Slot | Props | Description |
|------|------|-------------|
| `default` | - | `TxAvatar` children or compatible avatar VNodes. |

### Exposed Methods

No public instance methods are exposed.

## Style Customization

| Variable | Written by | Purpose |
|----------|------------|---------|
| `--tx-avatar-size` | custom `size` | Avatar width and height. |
| `--tx-avatar-font-size` | custom `size` | Fallback text and icon font size. |
| `--tx-avatar-status-size` | custom `size` | Status dot diameter. |
| `--tx-avatar-status-border` | custom `size` | Status dot border width. |
| `--tx-avatar-bg` | `backgroundColor` | Fallback background color. |
| `--tx-avatar-text` | `textColor` with `backgroundColor` | Fallback text color. |
| `--tx-avatar-group-overlap` | `TxAvatarGroup.overlap` | Exposes the resolved overlap distance on the group root. |
| `--tx-avatar-group-border` | caller / theme | Border color for grouped avatar items. |

Preset internals also use `--tx-avatar-size-preset`, `--tx-avatar-font-size-preset`, `--tx-avatar-status-size-preset`, and `--tx-avatar-status-border-preset`; callers should prefer the `size` prop over setting these directly.

## Best Practices

- Prefer `name` fallbacks for generated identity marks instead of hard-coded initials.
- Always provide meaningful `alt` when `src` represents a real user or account image.
- Use `status` only for presence or availability; use `TxStatusBadge` for textual system state.
- Avoid relying on `clickable` for primary actions. Pair avatars with a semantic `TxButton` when keyboard accessibility or clear action semantics are required.
- In groups, let the group inject `size` unless a specific child intentionally needs a different scale.

## Review Notes

- Reviewed against `packages/tuffex/packages/components/src/avatar/src/types.ts`, `TxAvatar.vue`, `TxAvatarGroup.vue`, and `avatar.test.ts`.
- API headings now use shared `Props`, `Events`, and `Slots` sections with per-component subsections so automated coverage checks and readers both find the contracts.
- Verified source behavior: image fallback order, initials generation, custom size normalization, click gating, group `max` overflow, group size injection, and overlap CSS variable.
- **Verified coverage:** Coverage: `packages/tuffex/packages/components/src/avatar/__tests__/avatar.test.ts` covers initials/custom colors, image error fallback, slot priority, custom size normalization, click gating, and group overflow.
- Accessibility boundary: the component forwards image `alt`, but the root remains a non-semantic `div`; use a real button/link when the avatar is the primary action.

